       Tunable laser spectrometers for Earth studies:
     * ALIAS   Aircraft Laser Infrared Absorption Spectrometer for the
       ER-2: HCl, N[2]O, CH[4], CO, NO[2]
       and isotopic water HDO/H[2]O measurements on the WB57F aircraft.
     * ALIAS II Airborne Laser Infrared Absorption Spectrometer-II for
       balloon and UAV: N[2]O, CH[4], and HCl.

     * ER-2, DC-8, and WB57 aircraft: JPL Near-IR Laser Spectrometers for
       stratospheric and tropospheric H[2]O measurements.
     * Aircraft Laser Isotope Spectrometer (ALIS)  for ^13CO[2]/^12CO[2]
       measurements on the WB-57F and DC-8 aircraft.

     * WISP   Water Isotope Spectrometer for HDO/H[2]O measurements of the
       Earth's upper troposphere.

     * BLISS   Balloon-borne Laser In Situ Spectrometer for Earth's
       stratosphere: HCl, N[2]O, CH[4], CO, NO[2],^ NO, HNO[3.]

     * UAV   Atmospheric Water and Climate Change:  A UAV Science
       Demonstration.
     * CO[2] Laser Absorption Spectrometer for profiling CO[2] in Earth's
       troposphere

